+You are an expert in genetic programming for trading strategies.
+
+Task: Extend scripts/evolution_engine.py to add proper crossover (recombination) and improve mutation — while preserving full compatibility with GPTreeStrategy.evaluate_node.
+
+Existing file contains:
+- generate_random_tree, mutate_tree, save_current_genome, run_backtest, calculate_fitness, etc.
+- Tree nodes use dicts with "primitive"/"operator", "parameters", "left"/"right" (for comparators), "children" (for operators)
+
+New requirements – add or update:
+
+1. def crossover_trees(tree1: dict, tree2: dict) -> tuple[dict, dict]:
+   - Return two new trees (deep copies of originals) after subtree crossover
+   - Select one random subtree node from tree1 and one from tree2 (uniform over all nodes)
+   - To select nodes: implement helper def get_all_nodes(tree: dict) -> list[dict] and def get_parent_info(tree: dict, target_node: dict) -> tuple[dict | None, str | int | None]
+   - Swap the two selected subtrees (replace in-place on deep copies)
+   - Integrity check before swap:
+     - Both nodes must return the same type (boolean or numeric)
+     - Categorize nodes:
+       - Boolean-returning: any "operator" node ("AND","OR","NOT"), or any "primitive" that is a comparator ("GREATER_THAN", etc.)
+       - Numeric-returning: any "primitive" that is an indicator ("RSI","EMA","SMA","BB_*")
+     - Only allow swap if both nodes are in the same category (boolean ↔ boolean or numeric ↔ numeric)
+     - If types mismatch → skip this pair and retry selection (max 10 attempts, else return original copies unchanged)
+   - Use copy.deepcopy on both input trees before modification
+
+2. Update reproduction logic (add or modify run_evolution / generate_offspring function):
+   - When creating a new individual:
+     - With probability 0.7: select two parents → perform crossover_trees(parent1, parent2) → take one of the two offspring
+     - With probability 0.3: select one parent → apply mutate_tree(parent)
+   - Ensure population diversity: avoid exact duplicates if possible
+
+3. Upgrade point mutation in mutate_tree / new helper _apply_mutation:
+   - Add "Comparator Swap" mutation type (probability ~20% when point-mutating a comparator node):
+     - If node["primitive"] in ["GREATER_THAN", "LESS_THAN", "CROSS_UP", "CROSS_DOWN"]
+     - Change it to a different one from the COMPARATORS list (uniform random among the other 3)
+
+Constraints:
+- All modifications must use copy.deepcopy to avoid mutating original trees/population
+- Maintain exact node structure expected by GPTreeStrategy.evaluate_node
+- Never produce structurally invalid trees (wrong child count, missing keys)
+- Add short docstrings and type hints to new functions
+- Prefer simplicity: if crossover selection fails after retries, fall back to mutation or cloning

