+### [ROLE: LEAD AI SYSTEMS INTEGRATOR] ###
+# GOAL: Phase 4 - Implement `scripts/ai_batch_generator.py` with secure key loading, a 30-minute strike system, and delimiter extraction.
+
+/create scripts/ai_batch_generator.py
+
+# 1. IMPORTS & SECURE SETUP:
+# - Import `json`, `sys`, `os`, `time`, `requests`, `re`.
+# - Import `BLOCK_REGISTRY` from `user_data.strategies.gp_blocks`.
+# - SECURE KEY LOADING: Read `user_data/api_keys.json`. If it doesn't exist, `sys.exit("Error: user_data/api_keys.json missing.")`. 
+#   Extract the list of keys from the `"api_keys"` field.
+
+# 2. THE DIVERSITY & KEY ROUTER:
+# - Load `user_data/logs/ai_payload_cache.json`.
+# - Extract `static_anchor`, `dynamic_tail`, and `current_generation`.
+# - MODEL ROUTER: `model = "gemini-3-flash-preview" if current_generation % 3 == 0 else "gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview"`
+# - KEY ROUTER: Select a key using modulo: `api_key = api_keys[current_generation % len(api_keys)]`
+# - CUSTOM DELIMITER INJECTION: Append this EXACT string to the `dynamic_tail`:
+#   "\n\nCRITICAL INSTRUCTION: You MUST wrap your entire JSON array between the exact text @@@JSON_START@@@ and @@@JSON_END@@@. Do not output anything outside of these tags."
+
+# 3. THE TIME-BASED STRIKE SYSTEM (`check_strikes()` and `add_strike()`):
+# - Create a function that reads a list of timestamps from `user_data/logs/strikes.json` (create if missing).
+# - Filter out timestamps older than 1800 seconds (30 minutes).
+# - If `len(recent_strikes) >= 10`: `sys.exit("🚨 FATAL: 10 AI HALLUCINATION STRIKES IN 30 MINS. HALTING ENGINE. 🚨")`.
+# - If validation fails, append `time.time()` to the list and save back to `strikes.json`.
+
+# 4. THE API CALLER & EXTRACTOR:
+# - Create `call_gemini(api_key, model, system_prompt, user_prompt)`.
+# - Construct the REST POST to `https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/models/{model}:generateContent?key={api_key}`.
+# - Payload format:
+#   `{"system_instruction": {"parts": [{"text": system_prompt}]}, "contents": [{"parts": [{"text": user_prompt}]}], "generationConfig": {"temperature": 0.7}}`
+# - Extract the text from the response. 
+# - Use `text.split("@@@JSON_START@@@")[1].split("@@@JSON_END@@@")[0].strip()` to safely extract the JSON.
+
+# 5. THE MAIN VALIDATION LOOP:
+# - Create a loop that attempts the API call up to 3 times per execution.
+# - Start of loop: call `check_strikes()`.
+# - Try to `json.loads()` the extracted text.
+# - VALIDATION 1: Must be a list of 5 objects containing 'type', 'entry_tree', 'exit_tree'.
+# - VALIDATION 2 (TUNGSTEN GUARD): Recursively scan trees; every `primitive` MUST exist in `BLOCK_REGISTRY`.
+# - IF PASS: Save the array to `user_data/strategies/latest_ai_batch.json` and `sys.exit(0)`.
+# - IF FAIL: Call `add_strike()`, print the exact validation error, `time.sleep(5)`, and loop again.
+
+# 6. RELIABILITY:
+# - Do not commit `user_data/api_keys.json` under any circumstances.
+# - Run `python3 scripts/ai_batch_generator.py` to test the connection.
+# - ON SUCCESS: `git add scripts/ai_batch_generator.py && git commit -m "Engine V2: Implemented Secure AI Batch Generator"`.

