+### [ROLE: LEAD QUANT DATA ARCHITECT] ###
+# GOAL: Phase 2.1 Retry - Implement the Generation Ledger (generation_history.json).
+
+# 1. SETUP THE LEDGER LOGIC (`scripts/evolution_engine.py`):
+# - Add `import time` to the top of the file if missing.
+# - Create a function `update_ledger(gen_data: dict) -> None` right after `ensure_directories()`.
+# - The function must load `PROJECT_ROOT / "user_data" / "logs" / "generation_history.json"`.
+# - If the file doesn't exist, initialize an empty list `[]`. Append `gen_data`, and save it back using `json.dump()`.
+
+# 2. CAPTURE DATA IN THE LOOP (`scripts/evolution_engine.py`):
+# - Inside `run_loop()`, at the very start of the `for _ in range(gens):` block, add: `generation_start_time = time.time()`
+# - Before the individual evaluation loop, define: `smoke_test_statuses = [None] * 6`
+# - Inside the evaluation loop, when the smoke test passes, set `smoke_test_statuses[i] = "passed"`. If it fails or times out, set it to `"failed"`.
+# - At the end of the generation loop (right before saving the population and state), calculate `execution_time = time.time() - generation_start_time`.
+# - Build a `gen_summary` dictionary capturing the gen_number, timestamp, execution_time, and a "slots" list detailing the lineage_id, fitness, and smoke_test status of all 6 slots.
+# - Call `update_ledger(gen_summary)`.
+
+# 3. IGNORE FILES:
+# - Add `user_data/logs/generation_history.json` to both `.gitignore` and `.aiderignore`.
+
+# 4. STRICT RELIABILITY CHECK (DO NOT COMMIT UNTIL THIS PASSES):
+# - Run: `grep -q "update_ledger" scripts/evolution_engine.py || exit 1`
+# - Run: `grep -q "generation_history.json" .gitignore || exit 1`
+# - Run: `./.venv/bin/python3 -m pytest tests/test_omniscience.py -v || exit 1`
+# - ONLY IF all commands succeed, run: `git add . && git commit -m "Engine V2.8: Implemented Master Generation Ledger"`

